{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The supplies were taken. Used weapons were left behind.{\r}

223
00:42:24,336 --> 00:42:27,622
酒馆滋事发生在黎明来之前 所以他们走不远
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The tavern events occurred before dawn, so they couldn't have got far.{\r}

224
00:42:27,840 --> 00:42:30,627
继续空中搜查 我肯定他们在什么时候...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Remain airborne for the moment. I'm sure they'll reappear...{\r}

225
00:42:30,843 --> 00:42:33,416
- ...会再次出现的 - 是，长官
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...in good time. - Yes, sir.{\r}

226
00:42:37,724 --> 00:42:40,560
我小时候见过这个东西
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've seen this before, when I was a child.{\r}

227
00:42:40,769 --> 00:42:42,311
我当时把它拿在手里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've held it.{\r}

228
00:42:42,521 --> 00:42:44,015
当时它就像这样打开着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}When it was open, like this.{\r}

229
00:42:44,231 --> 00:42:45,429
怎么可能呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How is that possible?{\r}

230
00:42:47,734 --> 00:42:49,442
我不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know.{\r}

231
00:42:51,780 --> 00:42:53,358
但我认识个可能知道的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But I know someone that might.{\r}

232
00:42:54,116 --> 00:42:56,073
安德雷斯・泰尼斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Andreas Tanis.{\r}

233
00:42:56,285 --> 00:42:59,120
他是联盟的官方史学家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was the official historian of the covens.{\r}

234
00:43:01,582 --> 00:43:05,200
因为他收录了维克多认为有恶意的谎言 所以失宠了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He fell from favour after documenting what Viktor considered malicious lies.{\r}

235
00:43:05,419 --> 00:43:08,336
当然，后来发现 诸多记载确有其事
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course, as it turns out, he was probably telling the truth.{\r}

236
00:43:08,547 --> 00:43:09,792
后来他怎么了？
