238
00:43:12,759 --> 00:43:14,040
300年了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Three hundred years?{\r}

239
00:43:14,261 --> 00:43:16,170
你怎么肯定我们现在能找到他？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What makes you think we'll find him now?{\r}

240
00:43:16,597 --> 00:43:18,007
是我押送流放他的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I was the one who exiled him.{\r}

241
00:43:57,554 --> 00:43:59,132
看起来像个修道院
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Looks like a monastery.{\r}

242
00:43:59,348 --> 00:44:01,387
以前是的 现在几乎变成了一所监狱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It used to be. More like a prison now.{\r}

243
00:44:02,059 --> 00:44:04,466
自从维克多下令以来 泰尼斯就一直在这里藏身
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tanis has been hiding there since Viktor's order.{\r}

244
00:44:04,686 --> 00:44:07,224
我们将会是 他在几个世纪以来首次看见的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll be the first people he's seen in centuries.{\r}

245
00:44:19,159 --> 00:44:21,199
- 真奇怪 - 怎么了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- That's odd. - What?{\r}

246
00:44:21,787 --> 00:44:24,360
我不记得以前有这扇门
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't remember this gate being here before.{\r}

247
00:44:26,667 --> 00:44:27,995
拿着这个
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Take this.{\r}

248
00:45:33,400 --> 00:45:34,775
妈的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Shit.{\r}

249
00:45:58,425 --> 00:45:59,540
回去！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go back!{\r}

250
00:46:01,970 --> 00:46:03,215
抓住你了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Gotcha.{\r}

251
00:46:06,266 --> 00:46:07,298
靠
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Fuck.{\r}

252
00:48:41,505 --> 00:48:43,628
我知道是你，塞琳娜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I knew it was you, Selene.{\r}

253
00:48:44,132 --> 00:48:47,383
你的血管里还散发着维克多身上的腥臭味
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The stench of Viktor's blood still lingers in your veins.{\r}

254
00:48:47,594 --> 00:48:49,053
泰尼斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tanis.{\r}

255
00:48:49,263 --> 00:48:50,971
我看你瞄准的功夫还没什么长进
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I see your aim hasn't improved.{\r}

256
00:48:53,267 --> 00:48:55,425
你一点都没变
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You haven't changed.{\r}

257
00:48:55,644 --> 00:48:57,352
你吓不倒我，塞琳娜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't scare me, Selene.{\r}

258
00:48:58,438 --> 00:49:00,265
好吧，那我们就试试看吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, we're gonna have to work on that.{\r}

259
00:49:10,450 --> 00:49:11,779
我们得谈谈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We need to talk.{\r}

260
00:49:15,914 --> 00:49:18,536
你的流放生活比我记忆中的好得多
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your exile seems a bit more comfortable than I remember.{\r}

261
00:49:19,459 --> 00:49:21,333
什么时候吸血鬼开始有狼人保镖了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How does a Vampire have Lycan bodyguards?{\r}

262
00:49:21,879 --> 00:49:22,958
他们是礼物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A gift.{\r}

263
00:49:23,172 --> 00:49:24,749
来自一个很有说服力的客户
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}From a most persuasive client.{\r}

264
00:49:25,966 --> 00:49:27,294
鲁深
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Lucian.{\r}

265
00:49:29,052 --> 00:49:31,425
为什么鲁深要保护你？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why would Lucian wanna protect you?{\r}

266
00:49:32,264 --> 00:49:33,806
因为他和他们有交易
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Because he was trading with them.{\r}

267
00:49:35,976 --> 00:49:37,969
紫外弹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}UV rounds.{\r}

268
00:49:38,187 --> 00:49:40,974
你残杀同类已经有多长时间了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How long have you been in the business of killing your own?{\r}

269
00:49:41,190 --> 00:49:44,107
我做的一切都是为了生存
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've done what's necessary to survive.{\r}

270
00:49:44,318 --> 00:49:48,612
你敬爱的维克多背叛了我 是他逼我这样做的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My decision was made easy the day your precious Viktor betrayed me.{\r}

271
00:49:48,822 --> 00:49:51,609
背叛可是他的专长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Betrayal was something he did very well.{\r}

272
00:49:52,993 --> 00:49:55,698
维克多死了，我杀的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Viktor's dead. I killed him.{\r}

273
00:49:55,913 --> 00:49:57,288
你？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You?{\r}

274
00:49:57,497 --> 00:49:59,241
杀了维克多？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Kill Viktor?{\r}

275
00:50:03,337 --> 00:50:05,294
不，我不相信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I think not.{\r}

276
00:50:07,508 --> 00:50:09,417
哦，除非你知道了真相
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, unless you've learned the truth.{\r}

277
00:50:14,806 --> 00:50:17,344
哦，老天有眼了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So your eyes are finally open.{\r}

278
00:50:18,143 --> 00:50:20,385
真相比光芒更难以接受...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't it interesting how the truth...{\r}

279
00:50:20,604 --> 00:50:22,929
...这难道不更有趣吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...is even harder to absorb than light?{\r}

280
00:50:23,148 --> 00:50:25,307
你知道，我当然也想阻止他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You know, I tried to stop him, of course.{\r}

281
00:50:25,526 --> 00:50:28,443
滑稽的是 他竟犯下如此重罪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A travesty, committing such a horrible crime.{\r}

282
00:50:29,530 --> 00:50:31,688
又轮到了你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And then turning you.{\r}

283
00:50:31,907 --> 00:50:33,983
承受这些太累了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That was too much to take.{\r}

284
00:50:34,243 --> 00:50:36,531
我抗议过 这也就是他为什么把我关在这里了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My protests are why he put me here.{\r}

285
00:50:37,538 --> 00:50:39,614
小心那个，亲爱的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Careful with that, dear.{\r}

286
00:50:39,831 --> 00:50:40,994
动静可是不小
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Makes a terrible bang.{\r}

287
00:50:42,376 --> 00:50:44,415
刀片打开时就会引爆的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Open the blades and they're active.{\r}

288
00:50:44,628 --> 00:50:46,537
多谢告知
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Good to know.{\r}

289
00:50:50,551 --> 00:50:53,124
维克多把你关在这里有他的理由 但是我想是...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Viktor put you here for a reason, but I doubt it was...{\r}

290
00:50:53,345 --> 00:50:55,634
...因为你心神不宁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...because you had moral qualms.{\r}

291
00:50:55,848 --> 00:50:59,845
- 你到底知道些什么？ - 我怕是几乎什么都不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- What do you know? - Very little of anything, I'm afraid.{\r}

292
00:51:06,191 --> 00:51:09,441
那是我看走眼了 你没有任何利用价值了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, then, perhaps I'm mistaken and there's no use for you at all.{\r}

293
00:51:10,737 --> 00:51:12,813
玛可斯想得到这个，为什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Marcus was after this. Why?{\r}

294
00:51:57,576 --> 00:52:00,363
有些历史是有事实根据的...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Some history is based on truth...{\r}

295
00:52:00,579 --> 00:52:02,655
...有些就是从谎言来的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and others on deception.{\r}

296
00:52:04,499 --> 00:52:08,082
维克多并不是你们所认为的 第一个吸血鬼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Viktor was not the first of our kind, as you were led to believe.{\r}

297
00:52:08,295 --> 00:52:10,204
他以前是一个人类...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was once human...{\r}

298
00:52:10,422 --> 00:52:12,580
...是这些土地的统治者
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...the ruler of these lands.{\r}

299
00:52:14,134 --> 00:52:15,878
玛可斯...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Marcus...{\r}

300
00:52:16,553 --> 00:52:18,427
...他才是真正的主
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...he's the one.{\r}

301
00:52:20,224 --> 00:52:21,504
是源头
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The source.{\r}

302
00:52:22,809 --> 00:52:24,767
第一的吸血鬼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The first true Vampire.{\r}

303
00:52:25,312 --> 00:52:27,637
那么那些传说是真的了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So the legend is true.{\r}

304
00:52:28,315 --> 00:52:31,601
在维克多无情生命的最后时期...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Toward the end of his ruthless life...{\r}

305
00:52:32,653 --> 00:52:36,781
...他的每一次呼吸都要比金银 还珍贵的时候...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...when the next breath meant more to Viktor than silver or gold...{\r}

306
00:52:36,990 --> 00:52:39,825
...玛可斯来到他身边...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...Marcus came with an offer...{\r}

307
00:52:40,035 --> 00:52:43,784
...带给他治疗疼痛和死亡的良方
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...a reprieve from sickness and death.{\r}

308
00:52:44,790 --> 00:52:46,284
长生不老
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Immortality.{\r}

309
00:52:46,500 --> 00:52:50,035
作为代价，维克多必须用他的 军队来帮助玛可斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And in return, Viktor was to use his army-turned-immortal to help him.{\r}

310
00:52:51,088 --> 00:52:52,712
帮他做什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}To do what?{\r}

311
00:52:52,923 --> 00:52:55,129
去击败狼人的祖先们...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}To defeat the very first Werewolves...{\r}

312
00:52:55,342 --> 00:52:58,343
...一群危险、极易繁殖的种族...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...a dangerous and infectious breed...{\r}

313
00:52:58,554 --> 00:53:01,127
...由玛可斯自己血肉所创造：
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...created by Marcus' own flesh and blood:{\r}

314
00:53:03,183 --> 00:53:04,761
那就是他的孪生兄弟威廉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}His twin brother, William.{\r}

315
00:53:06,770 --> 00:53:08,430
但是这些并非我们所知道的狼人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But these weren't the Lycans we know.{\r}

316
00:53:08,814 --> 00:53:11,020
也许听起来很恶心...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Disgusting though your brethren may be...{\r}

317
00:53:11,233 --> 00:53:13,190
...他们现在进化了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...they at least are evolved.{\r}

318
00:53:13,402 --> 00:53:15,644
不，他们一直就是狂怒的野兽
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, these were raging monsters.{\r}

319
00:53:15,863 --> 00:53:19,148
永远不会变回人形
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Never able to take human form again.{\r}

320
00:53:19,366 --> 00:53:22,486
只是最近他们的后代 学会了如何控制愤怒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It was only later generations that learned to channel their rage.{\r}

321
00:53:22,703 --> 00:53:26,403
而威廉的破坏和暴怒却是无止尽的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And William's appetite for destruction and rampage was insatiable.{\r}

322
00:53:27,708 --> 00:53:29,118
必须有人阻止他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He had to be stopped.{\r}

323
00:53:29,334 --> 00:53:31,742
一旦维克多的军队变成...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And so once Viktor's army was turned...{\r}

324
00:53:31,962 --> 00:53:34,334
...受他掌控的吸血鬼军团...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...the legions of Vampires under his control...{\r}

325
00:53:34,548 --> 00:53:37,751
...去追捕并杀死那些动物...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...tracked down and destroyed the animals...{\r}

326
00:53:37,968 --> 00:53:39,248
...他们就会捉到威廉...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...then captured William...{\r}

327
00:53:39,887 --> 00:53:41,345
...把他关入监狱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and locked him away.{\r}

328
00:53:41,889 --> 00:53:44,012
成为维克多永远的阶下囚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Viktor's prisoner for all time.{\r}

329
00:53:46,727 --> 00:53:47,925
为什么要让他活着？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why let him live?{\r}

330
00:53:48,145 --> 00:53:52,392
和维克多从来不敢对抗玛可斯的理由是一样的 恐惧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}For the very same reason that Viktor never conspired against Marcus: Fear.{\r}

331
00:53:52,733 --> 00:53:54,856
有人警告过他，如果玛可斯被杀死了...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was warned that, should Marcus be killed...{\r}

332
00:53:55,360 --> 00:53:58,361
...所有他吸血鬼的后裔都会一起死去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...all those in his bloodline would follow him to the grave.{\r}

333
00:53:59,448 --> 00:54:01,357
所以维克多认为...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So in Viktor's mind...{\r}

334
00:54:01,575 --> 00:54:04,280
...玛可斯的死 意味着所有狼人都会消失...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...William's death would mean the end for all Lycans...{\r}

335
00:54:04,494 --> 00:54:05,574
...也就是他所有的奴隶
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...his slaves.{\r}

336
00:54:07,664 --> 00:54:09,075
没错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

337
00:54:10,334 --> 00:54:12,410
是啊，一个很聪明的谎言...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, a clever deception...{\r}

338
00:54:12,628 --> 00:54:15,379
...但是维克多不敢以身试法
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...but one Viktor was hardly willing to put to the test.{\r}

339
00:54:16,757 --> 00:54:18,714
所以他要保护玛可斯...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And so Marcus was protected...{\r}

340
00:54:19,092 --> 00:54:21,132
...不顾一切
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...at all costs.{\r}

341
00:54:24,431 --> 00:54:25,629
找到了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, here we are.{\r}

342
00:54:31,438 --> 00:54:33,894
- 吸血鬼？ - 人类
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Vampires? - Mortals.{\r}

343
00:54:35,067 --> 00:54:38,068
效忠于亚历山大・柯文纳斯的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Men loyal to Alexander Corvinus.{\r}

344
00:54:39,947 --> 00:54:41,227
我们所有人的祖先
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The father of us all.{\r}

345
00:54:49,289 --> 00:54:50,570
这是什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's this?{\r}

346
00:54:54,461 --> 00:54:56,039
你应该知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You should know.{\r}

347
00:54:57,297 --> 00:54:59,041
这是威廉的监狱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's William's prison.{\r}

348
00:55:01,301 --> 00:55:05,002
你父亲奉命所建的监狱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The prison your father was commissioned to build.{\r}

349
00:55:10,561 --> 00:55:13,680
原来是你一直在为我看护着它 是吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So you've been the one keeping a watch over this for me, have you?{\r}

350
00:55:13,897 --> 00:55:16,471
我一直在到处找它，亲爱的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've been searching everywhere for this, my darling.{\r}

351
00:55:21,154 --> 00:55:22,353
怎么了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What is it?{\r}

352
00:55:23,073 --> 00:55:24,271
有什么事吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's wrong?{\r}

353
00:55:25,492 --> 00:55:28,327
她现在明白了为什么 她的家人都被屠杀了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She now understands why her family was killed.{\r}

354
00:55:31,331 --> 00:55:33,657
但那是好多年后的事情了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But that was many years later.{\r}

355
00:55:35,002 --> 00:55:36,828
鲁深逃跑的那个冬天
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The winter of Lucian's escape.{\r}

356
00:55:37,045 --> 00:55:39,038
你父亲知道太多的内情
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your father knew too much.{\r}

357
00:55:39,256 --> 00:55:40,999
或者对于维克多来说 他知道太多...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Or too much for Viktor to risk...{\r}

358
00:55:41,550 --> 00:55:43,293
...特别是当鲁西...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...especially when Lucian...{\r}

359
00:55:44,303 --> 00:55:47,588
...有了打开威廉监狱钥匙的时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...had the key to William's cell.{\r}

360
00:55:48,640 --> 00:55:50,467
而我就是通往监狱的地图
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I'm the map.{\r}

361
00:55:51,351 --> 00:55:52,846
没错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

362
00:55:53,896 --> 00:55:58,392
你是唯一知道监牢位置的幸存者
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The only one still living who has seen its location.{\r}

363
00:55:59,151 --> 00:56:02,152
哦，维克多认为你太小 不会记得很多...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, Viktor realized you'd be too young to remember explicitly...{\r}

364
00:56:02,362 --> 00:56:05,566
...但是玛可斯知道...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...but Marcus knows that the memory...{\r}

365
00:56:05,782 --> 00:56:09,401
...威廉监牢的具体位置...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and therefore the exact location of William's prison...{\r}

366
00:56:09,912 --> 00:56:11,738
...仍然储存在你的血液里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...is hidden away in your blood.{\r}

367
00:56:13,123 --> 00:56:15,448
为什么玛可斯现在要找到他...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why is Marcus looking for him now...{\r}

368
00:56:15,667 --> 00:56:17,210
...过了这么多年之后？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...after all this time?{\r}

369
00:56:17,628 --> 00:56:18,790
这个问题我无法回答
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That I cannot answer.{\r}

370
00:56:30,057 --> 00:56:31,634
不过我的确知道一个...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But I do know someone...{\r}

371
00:56:31,892 --> 00:56:34,679
...可以阻止他的人 或许我可以让你们见面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...who could stop him. Perhaps I could arrange a meeting.{\r}

372
00:56:36,313 --> 00:56:40,642
当然，作为交换的条件是 你可以放我一马
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}In exchange for your discretion, of course.{\r}

373
00:56:41,944 --> 00:56:43,402
当然可以
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course.{\r}

374
00:57:38,458 --> 00:57:41,376
泰尼斯，你看起来很紧张
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tanis. You seem anxious.{\r}

375
00:57:42,129 --> 00:57:44,371
为什么你一看见我就想跑呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why do you flee the very sight of me?{\r}

376
00:57:49,845 --> 00:57:51,007
请...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please...{\r}

377
00:57:52,139 --> 00:57:53,598
...坐
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...sit.{\r}

378
00:57:54,975 --> 00:57:57,727
我们的谈话不必如此不愉快
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no need for this to be unpleasant.{\r}

379
00:57:58,937 --> 00:58:01,393
你的陪伴对我而言 一直以来都是很愉快的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I've always rather enjoyed your company.{\r}

380
00:58:07,362 --> 00:58:09,485
你这样就太无礼了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Now you're being rude.{\r}

381
00:58:10,824 --> 00:58:12,283
对不起
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry.{\r}

382
00:58:20,501 --> 00:58:22,577
维克多一共做了两把钥匙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Viktor struck two keys.{\r}

383
00:58:23,170 --> 00:58:24,545
你都知道些什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you know of them?{\r}

384
00:58:26,673 --> 00:58:28,216
钥匙？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Keys?{\r}

385
00:58:29,176 --> 00:58:32,093
我不知道什么钥匙啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know of any keys.{\r}

386
00:58:47,694 --> 00:58:49,568
哦，对了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, yes.{\r}

387
00:58:49,780 --> 00:58:51,274
对了，那些钥匙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, those keys.{\r}

388
00:58:51,698 --> 00:58:54,616
- 是啊？ - 呃，一把...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Yes? - Well, one was...{\r}

389
00:58:56,161 --> 00:58:58,913
一把放在很显而易见的地方...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}One was kept in plain sight...{\r}

390
00:58:59,122 --> 00:59:01,329
...就在他孙女的脖子上...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...draped around his daughter's neck...{\r}

391
00:59:02,084 --> 00:59:04,539
...你一看就能看到 - 另一把呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...right there for you to see. - And the other?{\r}

392
00:59:07,256 --> 00:59:10,210
- 维克多总是带着它 - 在哪里？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Kept with Viktor at all times. - Where?{\r}

393
00:59:11,301 --> 00:59:13,009
在他身体里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Within him.{\r}

394
00:59:14,388 --> 00:59:16,012
在皮肉下面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Beneath the flesh.{\r}

395
00:59:22,437 --> 00:59:24,347
求你，求你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please. Please.{\r}

396
00:59:24,565 --> 00:59:25,679
求你了，不要
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I beg you. Please.{\r}

397
00:59:25,941 --> 00:59:27,768
不要，求你了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please, I beg you.{\r}

398
00:59:44,293 --> 00:59:46,914
- 可以阻止他的人 我可以让你们见面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Who could stop him. Perhaps I could arrange a meeting.{\r}

399
00:59:47,129 --> 00:59:49,584
去17号码头 找洛伦兹・马可
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go to pier 17. Ask for Lorenz Macaro.{\r}

400
01:00:13,989 --> 01:00:16,231
我们怎么知道泰尼斯不是在骗我们？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How do we know Tanis isn't setting us up?{\r}

401
01:00:16,450 --> 01:00:18,857
他还没有敢骗我的胆量
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's not brave enough to set me up.{\r}

402
01:00:22,998 --> 01:00:24,273
你们非法侵入这里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

403
01:00:24,823 --> 01:00:27,098
慢慢走出车子 以便让我看到你们的手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

404
01:00:27,911 --> 01:00:30,384
我们是来见洛伦兹・马可的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

405
01:00:30,621 --> 01:00:32,520
走出车子，慢慢地！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

406
01:00:32,627 --> 01:00:34,210
让我看到你们的手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

407
01:00:34,925 --> 01:00:37,307
想看看我们的手，是吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

408
01:00:44,686 --> 01:00:46,015
你们可以走了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can go.{\r}

409
01:00:56,490 --> 01:00:58,150
很熟悉吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're familiar with this, then?{\r}

410
01:01:06,124 --> 01:01:07,369
非常熟悉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Intimately.{\r}

411
01:01:14,675 --> 01:01:16,548
你是亚历山大・柯文纳斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're Alexander Corvinus.{\r}

412
01:01:21,849 --> 01:01:26,178
有个时期我叫过那名字
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There was a time that I was known by that name.{\r}

413
01:01:27,604 --> 01:01:30,938
不论叫什么，我始终是你的祖先
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}By any name, I am still your forefather.{\r}

414
01:01:37,072 --> 01:01:40,239
这些年来你是怎么隐藏你的行踪的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How have you stayed hidden all these years?{\r}

415
01:01:40,450 --> 01:01:42,941
几世纪以来，我一直在旁观 我的孩子...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}For centuries I've stood by and watched the havoc...{\r}

416
01:01:43,161 --> 01:01:48,120
...他们自己之间 还有给人类造成的巨大浩劫
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...my sons have wrought upon each other and upon humanity.{\r}

417
01:01:49,376 --> 01:01:51,167
这并非是那个早晨我迎接他们 来到这个世界上的时候...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Not the legacy I prayed for...{\r}

418
01:01:51,378 --> 01:01:53,620
...我所祈祷的遗赠
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...the morning I watched them enter this world.{\r}

419
01:01:54,923 --> 01:01:57,082
还有一项讨厌的职责...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And a tiresome duty...{\r}

420
01:01:57,301 --> 01:02:00,467
...抑止战争的爆发、清除混乱...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...keeping the war contained, cleaning up the mess...{\r}

421
01:02:01,513 --> 01:02:04,799
...掩藏我家族不幸的历史
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...hiding my family's unfortunate history.{\r}

422
01:02:05,017 --> 01:02:07,305
- 难道你没曾阻止过吗？ - 是啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Couldn't you have stopped it? - Yes.{\r}

423
01:02:08,604 --> 01:02:10,680
你们能杀了你自己的亲生儿子吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Could you kill your own sons?{\r}

424
01:02:10,898 --> 01:02:13,186
你明明知道玛可斯都会做些什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You know what Marcus will do.{\r}

425
01:02:13,400 --> 01:02:16,436
如果他找到我 他就找到了威廉监牢的位置
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}If he finds me, he finds William's prison.{\r}

426
01:02:16,653 --> 01:02:18,776
你一定要帮我们阻止他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You need to help us stop him.{\r}

427
01:02:20,115 --> 01:02:23,947
你来恳求我帮你杀了我的亲生儿子？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You are asking me to help you kill my son?{\r}

428
01:02:24,161 --> 01:02:25,536
你？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You?{\r}

429
01:02:25,746 --> 01:02:27,204
一个恶灵武士？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A Death Dealer?{\r}

430
01:02:27,581 --> 01:02:29,372
你在6个世纪里...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How many innocents did you kill...{\r}

431
01:02:29,583 --> 01:02:32,335
...为了给你的家族复仇 又杀死了多少人呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...in the six-century quest to avenge your family?{\r}

432
01:02:32,544 --> 01:02:34,869
别跟我来这套正义宣言
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Spare me your self-righteous declarations.{\r}

433
01:02:35,088 --> 01:02:40,130
你和玛可斯没有什么区别 甚至连威廉都不如
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You are no different from Marcus and even less noble than William.{\r}

434
01:02:40,344 --> 01:02:43,048
至少他是因为无法控制他的怒火
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}At least he cannot control his savagery.{\r}

435
01:02:43,263 --> 01:02:46,134
我所有的罪过都可以怪到你头上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Anything I've done can be laid at your feet.{\r}

436
01:02:46,350 --> 01:02:49,635
几十万人无辜被杀害 就是因为你无法接受...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hundreds of thousands have died because of your inability to accept...{\r}

437
01:02:49,853 --> 01:02:52,854
...你儿子是一个怪物的事实 而且他们还创造出更多的怪物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...that your sons are monsters, that they create monsters.{\r}

438
01:02:53,649 --> 01:02:55,191
你当初可以阻止这一切的发生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You could've stopped all of this.{\r}

439
01:02:55,400 --> 01:02:57,108
别因为你比你的对手弱小...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do not come grovelling to me...{\r}

440
01:02:57,319 --> 01:03:00,984
...就到我这里来娓娓乞求
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...simply because you are weaker than your adversary.{\r}

441
01:03:01,198 --> 01:03:04,152
你也知道威廉没有被关起来之前 造成的惨剧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You know the devastation William caused before he was captured.{\r}

442
01:03:04,368 --> 01:03:05,566
他不能被释放出来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He cannot be set free.{\r}

443
01:03:54,376 --> 01:03:56,949
哇...不，等等 你不是他的对手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wa... No, wait. You're no match for him.{\r}

444
01:04:19,860 --> 01:04:21,058
快了，兄弟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Soon, brother.{\r}

445
01:04:55,771 --> 01:04:57,395
不
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

446
01:05:09,326 --> 01:05:10,785
父亲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Father.{\r}

447
01:05:11,245 --> 01:05:12,276
不
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

448
01:05:13,747 --> 01:05:16,238
他们已经死了 好了，好了，我的孩子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They've gone. There, there, my child.{\r}

449
01:05:16,458 --> 01:05:17,917
你现在安全了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You are safe now.{\r}

450
01:06:06,633 --> 01:06:09,089
不要，麦克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No. Michael.{\r}

451
01:06:09,845 --> 01:06:11,090
看着我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look at me.{\r}

452
01:06:13,390 --> 01:06:14,932
麦克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Michael.{\r}

453
01:06:15,475 --> 01:06:16,674
妈的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Shit.{\r}

454
01:06:42,628 --> 01:06:44,336
快醒醒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please.{\r}

455
01:06:46,089 --> 01:06:47,999
醒醒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please.{\r}

456
01:06:57,017 --> 01:06:58,559
快啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on.{\r}

457
01:06:59,102 --> 01:07:00,762
快啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on.{\r}

458
01:07:04,358 --> 01:07:06,315
妈的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Fuck.{\r}

459
01:07:52,573 --> 01:07:53,853
你好，父亲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, Father.{\r}

460
01:07:54,491 --> 01:07:57,492
我不欢迎你的到来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You are unwelcome in my presence.{\r}

461
01:08:00,330 --> 01:08:04,245
一颗可以永不停息的心脏
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The predictable heart that never thaws.{\r}

462
01:08:04,918 --> 01:08:08,168
可惜在一个蠢人体内跳动
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Pity it beats within such a fool.{\r}

463
01:08:09,173 --> 01:08:10,916
不死族中的大长老...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The eldest of the immortals...{\r}

464
01:08:11,425 --> 01:08:15,339
...却从未尝试过去把握自己的命运
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...yet you have made no attempt to seize your destiny.{\r}

465
01:08:15,554 --> 01:08:20,893
我们是自然界中的异类 仅此而已
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We are oddities of nature, you and I. Nothing more.{\r}

466
01:08:21,101 --> 01:08:23,639
这是一个人类的世界
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is a world for humanity.{\r}

467
01:08:23,854 --> 01:08:27,982
你这些多愁善感 就是你抛弃你亲生儿子的原因？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And that petty sentiment explains why you rejected your sons?{\r}

468
01:08:28,192 --> 01:08:30,647
为什么你在过去半个世纪里...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why you stood by for over half a millennium...{\r}

469
01:08:30,861 --> 01:08:34,396
...让威廉独自在黑暗中受尽折磨？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...as William suffered alone in darkness?{\r}

470
01:08:34,948 --> 01:08:36,905
不，父亲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, Father.{\r}

471
01:08:37,576 --> 01:08:40,909
我对您的多愁善感无法苟同
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have no respect for your petty sentiment.{\r}

472
01:08:42,789 --> 01:08:45,625
维克多的钥匙，在哪儿？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Viktor's key. Where is it?{\r}

473
01:08:45,834 --> 01:08:48,586
无论你对威廉有怎样的计划 那都是没用的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Whatever plan you have for William is futile.{\r}

474
01:08:48,795 --> 01:08:51,915
- 你无法控制他 - 哦，我现在也更强壮了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- You cannot control your brother. - Oh, I am stronger now.{\r}

475
01:08:52,132 --> 01:08:55,501
而且我们的关系也远比 你原先想承认的要好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And our bond is greater than you have ever wanted to acknowledge.{\r}

476
01:08:55,719 --> 01:08:56,999
你错了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're wrong.{\r}

477
01:08:57,221 --> 01:09:00,424
不久，你就会像以前一样 失败的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Soon you'll be drowning in Lycans, just like before.{\r}

478
01:09:00,641 --> 01:09:02,265
哦，没有狼人了，父亲...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, not Lycans, Father...{\r}

479
01:09:02,684 --> 01:09:04,558
...也没有吸血鬼了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...or Vampires.{\r}

480
01:09:04,770 --> 01:09:09,266
一个新的种族 将由他们的制造者创造...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A new race, created in the image of their maker...{\r}

481
01:09:10,359 --> 01:09:11,983
...他们新的上帝：
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...their new god:{\r}

482
01:09:14,988 --> 01:09:16,945
那就是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Me.{\r}

483
01:09:28,877 --> 01:09:31,333
而真正的上帝...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And a true god...{\r}

484
01:09:36,051 --> 01:09:37,676
...是没有父亲的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...has no father.{\r}

485
01:10:13,839 --> 01:10:15,666
你必将失败
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You will fail.{\r}

486
01:10:51,543 --> 01:10:53,251
- 拿医疗箱来 - 不要
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Get the kit. - No.{\r}

487
01:11:00,636 --> 01:11:03,886
求你了，长官，让我们帮助你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please, sir, let us help you.{\r}

488
01:11:04,389 --> 01:11:06,382
我的期限已到，朋友
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The time has come, my friend.{\r}

489
01:11:08,018 --> 01:11:09,512
去找那个女孩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Find the girl.{\r}

490
01:11:10,938 --> 01:11:13,014
带她来见我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bring her to me.{\r}

491
01:11:18,529 --> 01:11:19,809
不，等一等
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, wait. Wait.{\r}

492
01:11:23,492 --> 01:11:26,612
如果你想找到玛可斯 你需要亚历山大的帮助
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}If you want Marcus, you'll need Alexander's help.{\r}

493
01:11:32,960 --> 01:11:34,418
不要把他留在这里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't leave him here.{\r}

494
01:11:55,107 --> 01:11:58,772
- 他得到挂件了吗？ - 是的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Did he get the pendant? - Yes.{\r}

495
01:11:59,570 --> 01:12:02,191
他对你一个人来说太强大了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's too powerful for you alone.{\r}

496
01:12:02,781 --> 01:12:04,821
你是唯一比他年长的人...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You are the only one older than he is...{\r}

497
01:12:05,033 --> 01:12:06,991
...也是唯一比他强壮的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...the only one stronger.{\r}

498
01:12:07,202 --> 01:12:09,574
你本可以亲自杀了他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You could have killed him yourself.{\r}

499
01:12:10,789 --> 01:12:13,790
不管他变成什么样...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No matter what he's become...{\r}

500
01:12:15,210 --> 01:12:16,586
...他始终是我的儿子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...he is my son.{\r}

501
01:12:22,926 --> 01:12:25,678
你是唯一的希望
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You are the last hope left.{\r}

502
01:12:26,638 --> 01:12:29,924
只有一种方法可以阻止他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There is only one way to defeat him.{\r}

503
01:12:37,274 --> 01:12:39,313
现在，快...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Quickly, now...{\r}

504
01:12:39,526 --> 01:12:43,476
...在我的血液里的遗赠消失之前
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...before there is no more legacy left in my veins.{\r}

505
01:12:52,039 --> 01:12:54,162
我会变成什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What will I become?{\r}

506
01:12:56,001 --> 01:12:57,626
未来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The future.{\r}

507
01:13:40,337 --> 01:13:42,246
现在去吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go now.{\r}

508
01:17:29,816 --> 01:17:31,275
我们已经接近了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We're getting close.{\r}

509
01:18:26,540 --> 01:18:28,746
调头，绕到河那边
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Head back around towards the river.{\r}

510
01:18:40,804 --> 01:18:42,880
我没有看到任何入口
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't see a way inside.{\r}

511
01:18:45,184 --> 01:18:47,390
以前应该有一个河道入口
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There used to be a river entrance just there.{\r}

512
01:18:47,603 --> 01:18:49,642
现在一定被淹没了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It must be submerged now.{\r}

513
01:18:49,855 --> 01:18:51,314
我们要潜水了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Looks like we're getting wet.{\r}

514
01:19:27,684 --> 01:19:29,227
准备好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Closer.{\r}

515
01:19:34,858 --> 01:19:36,400
塞琳娜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Selene.{\r}

516
01:20:49,641 --> 01:20:50,922
威廉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}William.{\r}

517
01:21:06,450 --> 01:21:07,944
等等
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wait.{\r}

518
01:21:12,998 --> 01:21:14,457
不要，威廉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, William. Stop.{\r}

519
01:21:15,000 --> 01:21:16,578
停下,兄弟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Be still, brother.{\r}

520
01:21:16,793 --> 01:21:18,252
是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's me.{\r}

521
01:21:21,924 --> 01:21:24,593
我是不会伤害你的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd no sooner harm you than myself.{\r}

522
01:21:57,084 --> 01:21:58,282
往哪边走？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Which way?{\r}

523
01:22:26,280 --> 01:22:28,071
就是这里？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Is this it?{\r}

524
01:22:32,369 --> 01:22:34,243
他已经到了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's already here.{\r}

525
01:23:08,071 --> 01:23:09,779
那是什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What is that?{\r}

526
01:23:09,990 --> 01:23:13,193
没什么，我们走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing. Let's go.{\r}

527
01:23:24,296 --> 01:23:26,419
我们太迟了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We're too late.{\r}

528
01:23:54,034 --> 01:23:55,612
- 跟着他 - 到他后面
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- After him. - Get behind him.{\r}

529
01:24:05,045 --> 01:24:06,670
令人刮目相看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Impressive.{\r}

530
01:25:15,616 --> 01:25:17,074
麦克，你是一个独一无二的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Michael, you're unique.{\r}

531
01:25:19,620 --> 01:25:22,241
以前从未有过混血儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's never been a hybrid before.{\r}

532
01:25:23,373 --> 01:25:25,117
你的力量是无限的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your powers could be limitless.{\r}

533
01:25:42,601 --> 01:25:44,807
不要开火！哦，妈的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold it! Oh, fuck.{\r}

534
01:25:48,565 --> 01:25:51,317
- 他在哪里？ - 穿过那里跑了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}- Where is he? - He went right through there.{\r}

535
01:25:53,028 --> 01:25:55,780
我们只有UV子弹，这并不能杀死他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All we have are UV rounds. They won't take him down.{\r}

536
01:25:55,989 --> 01:25:58,445
的确不能，但至少会拖延一些时间
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, but they'll slow him down.{\r}

537
01:26:44,746 --> 01:26:46,371
我们走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go.{\r}

538
01:26:46,915 --> 01:26:48,113
你还好吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You all right?{\r}

539
01:28:05,035 --> 01:28:06,743
老天啊！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Jesus Christ!{\r}

540
01:29:58,524 --> 01:30:01,809
可这并不是我们知道的狼人 不，他们是疯狂的野兽
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But these weren't the Lycans we know. No, these were raging monsters.{\r}

541
01:30:02,027 --> 01:30:04,150
再也变不回人形
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Unable to take human form ever again.{\r}

542
01:30:54,621 --> 01:30:56,495
你在等什么？ 快开枪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you waiting for? Shoot them.{\r}

543
01:30:56,707 --> 01:30:59,411
我不能，会伤害到她
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't. Not without taking her out.{\r}

544
01:30:59,626 --> 01:31:00,789
我无法瞄准目标
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't get a shot.{\r}

545
01:31:52,554 --> 01:31:53,799
麦克
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Michael.{\r}

546
01:32:30,092 --> 01:32:32,168
保护她
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Take her down.{\r}

547
01:33:04,459 --> 01:33:05,455
切断缆绳！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Cut us loose!{\r}

548
01:33:09,214 --> 01:33:10,874
要坠毁了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We're going down!{\r}

549
01:34:50,524 --> 01:34:51,935
威廉！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}William!{\r}

550
01:35:02,578 --> 01:35:06,492
我就知道维克多当初把你 留下来当"宠物"是一个错误
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I knew Viktor made a mistake by keeping you as a pet.{\r}

551
01:35:07,040 --> 01:35:10,374
他应该把你和你的家人一起杀了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He should have killed you with the rest of your family.{\r}

552
01:37:58,754 --> 01:38:01,838
一个无法预知的未来在等待我们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}An unknown chapter lies ahead.{\r}

553
01:38:02,049 --> 01:38:05,299
随着种族之间分界线的日趋模糊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The lines that had divided the clans have now been blurred.{\r}

554
01:38:05,511 --> 01:38:08,428
明争暗斗在所难免
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Chaos and infighting are inevitable.{\r}

555
01:38:08,639 --> 01:38:12,173
唯一确定的就是我们仍将面对黑暗
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All that is certain is that darkness is still ahead.{\r}

556
01:38:12,392 --> 01:38:16,141
然而此时此刻，我第一次...
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But for now, for the first time...{\r}

557
01:38:16,355 --> 01:38:19,190
...在曙光中看到了希望
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...I look into the light with new hope.{\r}
